channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: Woman died after skin implant procedure
item.description: Former colleagues of a NSW body modifier have told a court he claimed a woman who died after he implanted a plastic snowflake under her skin actually succumbed to a drug overdose.

item.title: Philippines’ Manny Pacquiao to run for president in 2022
item.description: Philippine boxing superstar Manny Pacquiao has launched his presidential bid with vows to tackle poverty and corruption as he seeks to win over voters with his rags-to-riches story.

item.title: Qld denies plan to keep state closed
item.description: Annastacia Palaszczuk has hosed down reports the Queensland government had agreed to keep the state closed longer than planned.

item.title: Netflix dominates Emmys with ‘Crown’ sweep and ‘Queen’s Gambit’ win
item.description: Streaming giant Netflix dominated the Emmys on Sunday, finally winning television's biggest prizes with "The Crown" and "The Queen's Gambit" and bagging an all-time record-equaling awards haul at a scaled-down ceremony.

item.title: Victoria to freeze in ‘rollercoaster’ weather
item.description: Victorians have been told to brace themselves for a return to winter weather, with umbrellas recommended for any picnic-goers on the AFL Grand Final long weekend.

item.title: ‘Extremists’ blamed for Melbourne violence
item.description: Construction union boss John Setka has blamed “extremists” for manipulating CFMEU members during a violent protest in Melbourne.

item.title: Babysitter facing almost 200 sex charges
item.description: A babysitter is facing almost 200 child sex charges that allegedly involve 12 complainants, including one who is just eight months old.

item.title: Family breaks silence on killer carer
item.description: The family of an Adelaide woman killed by her disability support worker who failed to care for her have spoken publicly for the first time.

item.title: Wallabies beast ready to end four-year hiatus
item.description: Sean McMahon hopes his trademark physicality can help the Aussies continue their winning ways, should he earn a Wallabies recall this Rugby Championship.

item.title: Mother confronts daughter’s murderer
item.description: A grieving mother has confronted the Muay Thai expert who brutally bashed her daughter to death during a drug-addled rage, telling a court of the heartbreak that had rippled through her family’s life.
